webpackJsonp([0xb6261ea223c4],{9142:function(e,t){e.exports={pathContext:{group:[{node:{fields:{title:"Time to relax",date:"03 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-03-time-to-relax/",tags:"Y2001"},html:'<p><a href="http://www.quotegeek.com/Literature/Churchill_Winston/">Winston Churchill</a>: "Indeed, it has been said that democracy is the worst form of Government except all those other forms that have been tried from time to time."</p>\n<p>Today is a normal workday in Germany, of course, but I did my best to work <i>independently</i>!</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Back in black",date:"02 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-02-back-in-black/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Cut the cord",date:"07 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-07-cut-the-cord/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Back in black",date:"02 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-02-back-in-black/",tags:"Y2001"},html:'<p>Another source of news from Germany in English is <a href="http://www.expatica.com/germany.asp">Expatica</a>. For example: <a href="http://www.expatica.com/germanymain.asp?pad=190,205,&item_id=10966">Wild housecats terrify students in Bamberg</a>. </p>\n<p>More to the point for us is a report on <a href="http://www.expatica.com/germanymain.asp?pad=197,212,&item_id=10961">German Hausfrauenkultur (Housewives\' Culture)</a>. German women are expected to stay home and care for their children until they are out of school. Luckily we can afford an alternative. </p>\n<p>I\'m (mostly) back up and around, just in time for the work week. Sounds like I missed a good picnic yesterday. The big kids were all playing on a slide too big for Christopher, so he made his own slide on a little hill on the ground, sliding down face first. He came home dirty and exhausted.</p>\n<p>Putting heat in perspective: Having lived in both Minnesota and Arizona, my personal feelings of hot and cold are somewhat extreme. I can\'t really use the word \'hot\' to describe any weather in Germany. For example, today is a pleasant, sunny north German summer day, 22&deg;C. According to <a href="http://hal.editthispage.com">Hal</a>, Sunday <a href="http://hal.editthispage.com/2001/07/01">evening</a> in Las Vegas was nearly twice as warm: 43&deg;C (109&deg;F) at 9pm. But in the desert it\'s a dry heat.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Sick day",date:"01 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-01-sick-day/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Time to relax",date:"03 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-03-time-to-relax/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Sick day",date:"01 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-01-sick-day/",tags:"Y2001"},html:"<p>My hay fever has developed into a full-blown bronchitis. I've spent most of the day in bed, and missed Christopher's day care summer picnic.</p>"},next:{fields:{title:"Safety first",date:"30 Jun 2001",slug:"/2001-06-30-safety-first/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Back in black",date:"02 Jul 2001",slug:"/2001-07-02-back-in-black/"}}}],pathPrefix:"",first:!1,last:!1,index:992,pageCount:1101}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---992-7ffb67db0e0cd01a8246.js.map